description: From Middle English unworship, unworschip, unworschipe, unworschippe, from Old English unworþsċyp, unworþsċype, unweorþsċipe, equivalent to un- +‎ worship.

entries.meaning: Lack of worship or respect; dishonour; failure or refusal to worship; irreverence.

verbs.description: unworship (third-person singular simple present unworships, present participle unworshipping or (US) unworshiping, simple past and past participle unworshipped or (US) unworshiped)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To deprive of worship or due honour; to dishonour.
